-- Telefonica shares fall after bid for Vivendi's Brazil unit GVT
-- 
-- Tue Aug 05, 2014 03:10AM EDT
-- None



MADRID, Aug 5 (Reuters) - Shares in Spain's largest telecommunications operator Telefonica <TEF.MC> dropped 1.5 pct in early trading on Tuesday after the company offered 6.7 billion euros ($9 billion) for France's Vivendi's Brazilian internet provider GVT.

